title: [Gleyminn Anni River, Shore]
description: Thick mud of varied earthen hues comprise a narrow shore at the end of a cavernous, mold-ridden passage.  Boulders and rubble block the way south, opposite a narrow passage that opens up beyond an old wooden sign splattered with mud.  A patchwork moldy fishing dock is barely visible beyond the passage as it widens to reveal a colorful marshland.
